  "clinical_criteria": [
    "More than 2 occurrences of Crohn's disease ICD-9 codes (555*)",
    "At least one medication from specified list",
    "For dual diagnosis cases: more than 2 ICD-9 codes for Ulcerative Colitis (556*)",
    "Manual curation required for dual diagnosis of Crohn's and UC",
    "Manual curation required for all possible/probable records"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "This Crohn's disease phenotype algorithm classifies patients into cases, possible/probable cases, and controls. Cases require more than 2 occurrences of ICD-9 codes 555* (Regional enteritis) AND at least one specified medication. Two subcases are defined: 1) Crohn's with medications only (excluding any UC codes 556*), and 2) Crohn's with medications plus UC diagnosis (requiring >2 UC codes). Possible/probable cases have ICD-9 codes but require manual review. Controls must have none of the case criteria and also exclude a comprehensive list of autoimmune/inflammatory conditions and related keywords. The algorithm includes extensive keyword searching in clinical notes and pathology reports, with manual curation requirements for complex cases.",
  "analysis_timestamp": "2026-01-29T02:53:37.869570Z"
